Table of Contents¶

Introduction¶

This dataset collects information from 100k medical appointments in Brazil and is focused on the question of whether or not patients show up for their appointment

Data Understanding¶

>

To understand the dataset better, I set out to answer the following questions:

  • What is the fraction of patients who miss their scheduled appointment?
  • What factors are important for us to know in order to predict if a patient will show up for their scheduled appointment?
  • What is the relationship between the various variables?

In [14]:
num_cols = numerical_cols.columns

def hist_plot(col):
    plt.figure( figsize=(10,5))
    plt.hist(data['{}'.format(col)]);
    plt.axvline(data['{}'.format(col)].mean(), color='red',linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1);
    plt.title("Histogram of {}".format(col));
    plt.xlabel('{}'.format(col));
    plt.ylabel("Frequency");
    plt.show();
In [15]:
for x in num_cols:
    hist_plot(x)

Research Question 4 (What is the relationship between the various variables?)¶

In [29]:
cor = data.corr()

plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))
sns.heatmap(cor, cbar=True,annot=True)
Out[29]:
<AxesSubplot:>

The correlation matrix shows the correlation values, which measure the degree of linear relationship between each pair of variables. The correlation values can fall between -1 and +1. The variables which tend to increase have a positive correlation. If one variable increases while the other variable decreases, the correlation value is negative.

Conclusions¶

Findings

  • 20% failed to turn up on the appointment date.
  • Most pf those who failed to turn up on the appointment date came from Jardin Camburi state
  • Youths had the highest number of missed appointments followed by children.
  • PatientID and appointmentID are not that significant in this investigation.
  • The features have a low correlation with each other.
  • Hypertension has a high correlation with age.
  • Most of the age distribution falls along the red line (all dots would fall on the red line if the distribution were perfectly normal, but the tails fall off dramatically from the normal)

Limitations¶

  • Analysis on date time objects i.e appointment and schedule day were not much performed.
  • The dataset is imbalanced in regards to the No-show feature.
